<div class="container">
  <h1>Voice Commands and Basic Voice Control</h1>
  <div class="content">
    <div class="text-container">
      <p>Welcome to the next lesson! In this lesson, we will discuss how to use voice commands to control your TV, including some basic voice commands that can make your viewing experience even easier.</p>

      <p>Many modern TVs come with a <strong>Voice Control button</strong> on the remote. This button is usually represented by a <strong>microphone icon</strong>. By pressing and holding this button, you can speak directly to your TV to perform various actions, such as changing channels, adjusting volume, or searching for content.</p>
      <div class="image-container">
      <%= image_tag 'tv_talking.png'; %>
    </div>
      <p>Here are some <strong>basic voice commands</strong> you can use:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>"Turn on the TV"</strong> or <strong>"Turn off the TV"</strong> - Use these commands to power the TV on or off.</li>
        <li><strong>"Increase the volume"</strong> or <strong>"Decrease the volume"</strong> - Use these commands to adjust the volume without pressing any buttons.</li>
        <li><strong>"Mute the TV"</strong> - This command will instantly mute the volume.</li>
        <li><strong>"Change to channel [channel number or name]"</strong> - You can switch to specific channels by stating the channel name or number.</li>
        <li><strong>"Open [app name]"</strong> - You can open apps like Netflix or YouTube by simply saying the app name.</li>
        <li><strong>"Search for [movie/show name]"</strong> - This command helps you search for a specific show or movie across all apps and live TV.</li>
      </ul>

      <p>Using voice commands can make navigating the TV easier, especially when searching for content or controlling basic settings. Just remember to press and hold the <strong>Voice Control button</strong> while speaking your command, and release it once you've finished.</p>


      <!-- Add quiz here -->
      <div class="quiz-container">
        <h2>Quiz: Test Your Knowledge!</h2>
        <p>1. What button do you press to use voice control?</p>
        <button onclick="checkAnswer(this, true)">The Voice Control button with a microphone icon</button>
        <button onclick="checkAnswer(this, false)">The Power button</button>
        <button onclick="checkAnswer(this, false)">The Volume button</button>

        <p>2. How do you change channels using voice commands?</p>
        <button onclick="checkAnswer(this, true)">Say "Change to channel [channel number or name]"</button>
        <button onclick="checkAnswer(this, false)">Say "Volume up"</button>
        <button onclick="checkAnswer(this, false)">Say "Mute the TV"</button>

        <p>3. Which command would you use to search for a movie?</p>
        <button onclick="checkAnswer(this, true)">"Search for [movie/show name]"</button>
        <button onclick="checkAnswer(this, false)">"Increase the volume"</button>
        <button onclick="checkAnswer(this, false)">"Turn off the TV"</button>
      </div>

      <p>Great job completing this lesson on using voice commands to control your TV! Feel free to go back to the TV homepage or move on to the next lesson.</p>
      <div class="button-container">
        <a href="<%= tv_course_path %>" class="button">Back to TV Modules</a>
        <a href="<%= tv_settings_path %>" class="button">Next Lesson</a>
      </div>
    </div>


  </div>
</div>

